Plotting with openair: Exercises

Exercises

These exercises accompany the Plotting with openair tutorial.

  1. Use the summaryPlot() function to visualize the chicago_wind dataset.

Solution

  1. Use the windRose() function on the chicago_wind dataset and split the data into different panels by season.

Solution

  1. Use the pollutionRose() function for the ozone column in the chicago_wind dataset and change the statistic parameter to prop.mean.

Solution

  1. Use dplyr to subset airdata down to ozone values (parameter 44201) and sites c("840170890005", "840170971007", "840171110001"). Then use tidyr to convert the data to a wide format. Plot the three time series using the timePlot() function in openair. First plot the raw hourly data, then use the avg.time parameter to plot daily, weekly, and monthly values.

Solution

Solutions

Solution 1

library(region5air)
library(openair)
data(chicago_wind)
chicago_wind$date <- substr(chicago_wind$datetime, 1, 13)
chicago_wind$date <- as.POSIXct(chicago_wind$date, format = "%Y%m%dT%H%M",
                                tz = "America/Chicago")
wind <- select(chicago_wind, date, wind_speed, wind_dir, ozone)
summaryPlot(wind)
##      date1      date2 wind_speed   wind_dir      ozone 
##  "POSIXct"   "POSIXt"  "numeric"  "numeric"  "numeric"

Solution 2

Using the wind data frame from Solution 1,

names(wind)[1:3] <- c("date", "ws", "wd")
windRose(wind, type = "season", key.footer = "knots")

Solution 3

First lets plot with the default statistic of prop.count.

pollutionRose(wind, pollutant = "ozone", statistic = "prop.count")

pollutionRose(wind, pollutant = "ozone", statistic = "prop.mean")

Solution 4

library(tidyr)
ozone <- filter(airdata, 
                site %in% c("840170890005", "840170971007", "840171110001"),
                parameter == 44201)
ozone$date <- as.POSIXct(ozone$datetime, format = "%Y%m%dT%H%M",
                                tz = "America/Chicago")
# some dates weren't converted--remove those
ozone <- filter(ozone, !is.na(date))
ozone <- select(ozone, site, date, value)
ozone <- spread(ozone, site, value)
timePlot(ozone, pollutant = c("840170890005", "840170971007", "840171110001"))

timePlot(ozone, pollutant = c("840170890005", "840170971007", "840171110001"),
         avg.time = "day")

timePlot(ozone, pollutant = c("840170890005", "840170971007", "840171110001"),
         avg.time = "week")

timePlot(ozone, pollutant = c("840170890005", "840170971007", "840171110001"),
         avg.time = "month")
